The paper deals with the capacity region of the interference channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on the cognitive interference channel, which is a subcategory of interference channels that involves one transmitter non-causally knowing the message of the other. This falls under the subcategory of network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also mentions achievable rate regions and outer bounds, which are common concepts in coding theory (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the capacity region of the Gaussian cognitive interference channel, which involves signal processing (cs.SI) and communication and information theory (cs.CC).
